  "puzzle": {
    "type": "ice_sliding",
    "description": "Two large ice floors on 1F. The player slides uncontrollably on ice tiles until hitting a wall or solid ground. Navigating both ice floors is required to reach the stairs to B1F and ultimately the Blackthorn exit. No Strength boulders on 1F."
  },
  "notes": "Ice Path 1F (20x18 blocks, 40x36 tiles) is the entrance floor of the Ice Path cave connecting Route 44 (west) to Blackthorn City (east). Tileset: TILESET_ICE_PATH. Music: MUSIC_DARK_CAVE. The cave landmark is LANDMARK_ICE_PATH. The floor has two large ice-sliding puzzle areas and a narrow eastern corridor. HM07 Waterfall is the key item found here — required for the final passage to Blackthorn. No trainers are present in the Ice Path at all. Three item balls: HM07 at (31,7), Protein at (35,9), PP Up at (32,23). Two holes lead down to B1F at (37,5) and (37,13). Wild encounters include Swinub (Ice/Ground type, exclusive to Ice Path), Zubat, and Golbat during day/morning; Delibird replaces Swinub at night. Fishing group DRATINI gives access to Dratini and Dragonair but there is no water on 1F."
